  "intent_precise": "Automated Sample Prep for GNA Octea [v2]: Using magPlate (deep_well_plate, slot 3), tempPlate (labware, slot 4), rsvr (reservoir, slot 10), tubeRack (tuberack, slot 6). With magnetic module, temperature module. (1) Transfer 90\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (2) Mix wells multiple wells in plate, 3 cycles at 20\u00b5L. (3) Transfer 20\u00b5L from source to destination. (4) Transfer 170\u00b5L from source to destination. (5) Mix 10 times at 180\u00b5L. (6) Wait 1 seconds. (7) Set temperature to 80\u00b0C. (8) Incubate for 3 minutes. (9) Mix 5 times at 180\u00b5L. (10) Wait 1 seconds. (11) Adjust temperature. (12) Incubate for 3 minutes. (13) Mix 3 times at 180\u00b5L. (14) Transfer 200\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (15) Engage magnets for bead separation. (16) Incubate for 2 minutes. (17) Transfer 160\u00b5L from source to destination. (18) Disengage magnets to release beads. (19) Transfer 200\u00b5L from source to destination. (20) Transfer 150\u00b5L from source to destination. (21) Wait 2 seconds. (22) Engage magnets for bead separation. (23) Incubate for 2 minutes. (24) Transfer 200\u00b5L from source to destination. (25) Disengage magnets to release beads. (26) Transfer 175\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (27) Mix 6 times at 180\u00b5L. (28) Transfer 40\u00b5L from source to destination. (29) Transfer 30\u00b5L from source to destination. (30) Wait 1 seconds. (31) Transfer 40\u00b5L from source to destination.",
  "intent_concise": "Perform magnetic bead separation, temperature control (80\u00b0C). (volumes 10\u00b5L-200\u00b5L, ~13 min total)",
  "intent": "For the Automated Sample Prep for GNA Octea v2 protocol, set up your magnetic module with the deep well plate in slot 3, temperature module with labware in slot 4, reservoir in slot 10, and tube rack in slot 6. Start by transferring 90\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1, then perform multiple mixing cycles (3 cycles at 20\u00b5L), followed by sequential transfers of 20\u00b5L and 170\u00b5L with mixing 10 times at 180\u00b5L after a 1-second wait. Heat the samples to 80\u00b0C and incubate for 3 minutes, mix 5 times at 180\u00b5L, wait 1 second, adjust temperature and incubate for another 3 minutes, then mix 3 times at 180\u00b5L before transferring 200\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. Complete the protocol with magnetic bead separations (engaging magnets for 2-minute incubations), alternating transfers of 160\u00b5L, 200\u00b5L, 150\u00b5L, 200\u00b5L, and 175\u00b5L with appropriate waiting periods, finishing with mixing 6 times at 180\u00b5L and final transfers of 40\u00b5L, 30\u00b5L, and 40\u00b5L after 1-second waits.",
